summary.intent: User wanted to commit and push changes after resolving a merge conflict in manual_commit_git.go, ensuring both the resolveAgentType helper and new userPrompt parameter from main were integrated.
summary.outcome: Successfully merged origin/main, resolved the conflict by combining local changes with upstream parameter additions, updated test file to match the new signature, and pushed all changes. All tests and linting passed.

repo: The codebase uses a userPrompt parameter that needed to be threaded through manual commit functions
Test files must be updated when function signatures change to include new parameters like userPrompt

code.finding: Merge resolution required combining local resolveAgentType helper with upstream userPrompt parameter additions
Test file required userPrompt parameter to be added to match updated function signature

workflow: IDE LSP diagnostics (gopls) can show stale errors after merge conflicts are resolved, even when actual build/lint pass
Running linter after test file fixes helps verify all changes are consistent before committing

friction: Stale LSP diagnostics caused confusion about whether merge conflicts remained after successful push
Test file wasn't initially updated with the new parameter, causing linter failure
